mods:titleInfo.mods:title: Preservation copy: Pair of cast-iron pipe arches under construction across Rock Creek with a packet boat in the foreground. Officially called the Washington Aqueduct Bridge No. 6, this structure would later be incorporated into what is today the Pennsylvania Avenue Bridge.
